Sentencas: La2NiO4+delta, a mixed ionic-electronic conducting oxide with K2NiF4 type structure, has been studied as cathode material with La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 (LSGM) electrolyte for intermediate solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: La2NiO4+δ potential cathode material on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: XRD results reveal excellent chemical compatibility between the La2NiO4+delta sample and LSGM electrolyte.
Titulo: La2NiO4+δ potential cathode material on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A single cell (0.22 cm(2) active area) was fabricated with La2NiO4+delta as cathode, Ni-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (2:1; w/w) as anode and LSGM as electrolyte.
Titulo: La2NiO4+δ potential cathode material on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A thin buffer layer of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) between anode and electrolyte was used to avoid possible interfacial reactions.
Titulo: La2NiO4+δ potential cathode material on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The cell was tested under humidified H-2 and stationary air as fuel and oxidant, respectively.
Titulo: La2NiO4+δ potential cathode material on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The electrochemical behaviour was evaluated by means of current-voltage curves and impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: La2NiO4+δ potential cathode material on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Microstructure and morphology of the cell components were analysed by SEM-EDX after testing.
Titulo: La2NiO4+δ potential cathode material on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The maximum power densities were 160, 226, and 322 mW cm(-2) at 750, 800 and 850 degrees C, respectively with total polarisation resistances of 0.77, 0.48 and 0.31 Omega cm(2) at these temperatures.
Titulo: La2NiO4+δ potential cathode material on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Cell performance remained stable when a current density of 448 mA cm(-2) was demanded for 144h at 800 degrees C, causing no apparent degradation in the cell.
Titulo: La2NiO4+δ potential cathode material on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The performance of this material may be further improved by reducing the electrolyte thickness and optimisation of the electrode microstructure.
Titulo: La2NiO4+δ potential cathode material on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell
